      <title class="- topic/title " xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/rule-creator-guide/concepts/c_rule-design-patterns.dita" xtrc="title:5;127:14">Pattern 3: Check date freshness</title>
      <p class="- topic/p " xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/rule-creator-guide/concepts/c_rule-design-patterns.dita" xtrc="p:5;128:10">Use the <codeph class="+ topic/ph pr-d/codeph " xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/rule-creator-guide/concepts/c_rule-design-patterns.dita" xtrc="codeph:5;128:26">date</codeph> flag with the <codeph class="+ topic/ph pr-d/codeph " xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/rule-creator-guide/concepts/c_rule-design-patterns.dita" xtrc="codeph:6;128:62">&lt;</codeph>
      operator. The <codeph class="+ topic/ph pr-d/codeph " xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/rule-creator-guide/concepts/c_rule-design-patterns.dita" xtrc="codeph:7;129:29">value</codeph> is the maximum age in days.</p>

      <codeblock xml:space="preserve" class="+ topic/pre pr-d/codeblock " xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/rule-creator-guide/concepts/c_rule-design-patterns.dita" xtrc="codeblock:4;131:39">{
  "id": 3, "name": "ms-date-must-be-within-one-year", "type": "header",
  "query": "ms.date",
  "flag": "date", "operation": "&lt;", "value": "365",
  "level": "Suggested",
  "mitigation": "Update ms.date to today's date (YYYY-MM-DD format)."
}</codeblock>

      <p class="- topic/p " xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/rule-creator-guide/concepts/c_rule-design-patterns.dita" xtrc="p:6;139:10">The comparison is: <codeph class="+ topic/ph pr-d/codeph " xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/rule-creator-guide/concepts/c_rule-design-patterns.dita" xtrc="codeph:8;139:37">(today - ms.date).days &lt; 365</codeph>.</p>
    </section>

    <section id="pattern-heading-count" class="- topic/section " xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/rule-creator-guide/concepts/c_rule-design-patterns.dita" xtrc="section:5;142:41">
      <title class="- topic/title " xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/rule-creator-guide/concepts/c_rule-design-patterns.dita" xtrc="title:6;143:14">Pattern 4: Require exactly one H1</title>
      <p class="- topic/p " xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/rule-creator-guide/concepts/c_rule-design-patterns.dita" xtrc="p:7;144:10">Use the <codeph class="+ topic/ph pr-d/codeph " xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/rule-creator-guide/concepts/c_rule-design-patterns.dita" xtrc="codeph:9;144:26">count</codeph> flag on an XPath expression to count
      matching elements.</p>

      <codeblock xml:space="preserve" class="+ topic/pre pr-d/codeblock " xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/rule-creator-guide/concepts/c_rule-design-patterns.dita" xtrc="codeblock:5;147:39">{
  "id": 4, "name": "must-have-exactly-one-h1", "type": "body",
  "query": "/html/body/h1",
  "flag": "count", "operation": "==", "value": "1",
  "level": "Required",
  "mitigation": "The document must have exactly one H1 heading."
}</codeblock>
    </section>

    <section id="pattern-required-section" class="- topic/section " xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/rule-creator-guide/concepts/c_rule-design-patterns.dita" xtrc="section:6;156:44">
      <title class="- topic/title " xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/rule-creator-guide/concepts/c_rule-design-patterns.dita" xtrc="title:7;157:14">Pattern 5: Require a specific H2 section</title>
      <p class="- topic/p " xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/rule-creator-guide/concepts/c_rule-design-patterns.dita" xtrc="p:8;158:10">Use the <codeph class="+ topic/ph pr-d/codeph " xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/rule-creator-guide/concepts/c_rule-design-patterns.dita" xtrc="codeph:10;158:26">count</codeph> flag and XPath predicate to check that
      a specific section heading exists.</p>

      <codeblock xml:space="preserve" class="+ topic/pre pr-d/codeblock " xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/rule-creator-guide/concepts/c_rule-design-patterns.dita" xtrc="codeblock:6;161:39">{
  "id": 5, "name": "must-have-prerequisites-section", "type": "body",
  "query": "//h2[normalize-space(text())='Prerequisites']",
  "flag": "count", "operation": "&gt;", "value": "0",
  "level": "Required",
  "mitigation": "Add a '## Prerequisites' section to the document."
}</codeblock>
    </section>

    <section id="pattern-title-format" class="- topic/section " xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/rule-creator-guide/concepts/c_rule-design-patterns.dita" xtrc="section:7;170:40">
      <title class="- topic/title " xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/rule-creator-guide/concepts/c_rule-design-patterns.dita" xtrc="title:8;171:14">Pattern 6: Enforce an H1 naming convention</title>
      <p class="- topic/p " xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/rule-creator-guide/concepts/c_rule-design-patterns.dita" xtrc="p:9;172:10">Use the <codeph class="+ topic/ph pr-d/codeph " xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/rule-creator-guide/concepts/c_rule-design-patterns.dita" xtrc="codeph:11;172:26">text</codeph> flag with <codeph class="+ topic/ph pr-d/codeph " xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/rule-creator-guide/concepts/c_rule-design-patterns.dita" xtrc="codeph:12;172:58">[:</codeph> (starts with)
      to check the content of the H1.</p>

      <codeblock xml:space="preserve" class="+ topic/pre pr-d/codeblock " xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/rule-creator-guide/concepts/c_rule-design-patterns.dita" xtrc="codeblock:7;175:39">{
  "id": 6, "name": "h1-must-start-with-tutorial", "type": "body",
  "query": "/html/body/h1",
  "flag": "text", "operation": "[:", "value": "Tutorial:",
  "level": "Required",
  "mitigation": "H1 must begin with 'Tutorial:' for tutorial articles."
}</codeblock>
    </section>

    <section id="pattern-length-limit" class="- topic/section " xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/rule-creator-guide/concepts/c_rule-design-patterns.dita" xtrc="section:8;184:40">
      <title class="- topic/title " xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/rule-creator-guide/concepts/c_rule-design-patterns.dita" xtrc="title:9;185:14">Pattern 7: Limit title length</title>
      <p class="- topic/p " xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/rule-creator-guide/concepts/c_rule-design-patterns.dita" xtrc="p:10;186:10">Use the <codeph class="+ topic/ph pr-d/codeph " xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/rule-creator-guide/concepts/c_rule-design-patterns.dita" xtrc="codeph:13;186:26">l</codeph> operator (length limit) to ensure the H1
      text is under a character threshold.</p>

      <codeblock xml:space="preserve" class="+ topic/pre pr-d/codeblock " xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/rule-creator-guide/concepts/c_rule-design-patterns.dita" xtrc="codeblock:8;189:39">{
  "id": 7, "name": "h1-under-60-chars", "type": "body",
  "query": "/html/body/h1",
  "flag": "text", "operation": "l", "value": "60",
  "level": "Suggested",
  "mitigation": "H1 must be under 60 characters for SEO."
}</codeblock>
    </section>

    <section id="pattern-absence" class="- topic/section " xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/rule-creator-guide/concepts/c_rule-design-patterns.dita" xtrc="section:9;198:35">
      <title class="- topic/title " xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/rule-creator-guide/concepts/c_rule-design-patterns.dita" xtrc="title:10;199:14">Pattern 8: Absence checks (design smell — avoid until v0.3)</title>
      <note type="danger" class="- topic/note " xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/rule-creator-guide/concepts/c_rule-design-patterns.dita" xtrc="note:1;200:27"><b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b " xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/rule-creator-guide/concepts/c_rule-design-patterns.dita" xtrc="b:1;200:30">Do not use this pattern for new rules.</b>
      markdown-validator v0.2 has no negation operator. Expressing "this must
      NOT exist" requires a workflow-inversion technique that is fragile and
      easy to wire incorrectly. A <codeph class="+ topic/ph pr-d/codeph " xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/rule-creator-guide/concepts/c_rule-design-patterns.dita" xtrc="codeph:14;203:43">negate</codeph> flag is planned for
      v0.3 and will replace this entirely. See
      <xref href="c_known-limitations.dita" class="- topic/xref " xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/rule-creator-guide/concepts/c_rule-design-patterns.dita" xtrc="xref:9;205:45" type="concept"><?ditaot usertext?>Known limitations<?ditaot genshortdesc?><desc class="- topic/desc ">Understanding the current limitations of markdown-validator before   you write rules saves hours of debugging. Four limitations affect the types   of rules you can reliably express today.</desc></xref>.
      Only use the workaround below if you have an immediate need and cannot
      wait for v0.3. Track the v0.3 negation issue at
      <xref href="https://github.com/Final-State-Press/markdown-validator/issues" format="html" scope="external" class="- topic/xref " xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/rule-creator-guide/concepts/c_rule-design-patterns.dita" xtrc="xref:10;209:44"><?ditaot usertext?>github.com/Final-State-Press/markdown-validator/issues</xref>.</note>

      <p class="- topic/p " xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/rule-creator-guide/concepts/c_rule-design-patterns.dita" xtrc="p:11;211:10">To express "the title must NOT contain the word 'guide'," a workflow
      can invert a contains check using a known-passing sentinel rule. The
      inversion works by swapping which branch is "good": the True branch (word
      IS present — the bad state) is routed back to the failing rule, while the
      False branch (word is absent — the good state) routes to a sentinel that
      passes. <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b " xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/rule-creator-guide/concepts/c_rule-design-patterns.dita" xtrc="b:2;216:18">This is not standard workflow logic.</b> It exploits branching
      as a substitute for a missing operator.</p>

      <p class="- topic/p " xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/rule-creator-guide/concepts/c_rule-design-patterns.dita" xtrc="p:12;219:10">Assume rule 5 is a <codeph class="+ topic/ph pr-d/codeph " xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/rule-creator-guide/concepts/c_rule-design-patterns.dita" xtrc="codeph:15;219:37">text</codeph> / <codeph class="+ topic/ph pr-d/codeph " xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/rule-creator-guide/concepts/c_rule-design-patterns.dita" xtrc="codeph:16;219:61">]:</codeph>
      (contains) check on the H1 for the string <codeph class="+ topic/ph pr-d/codeph " xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/rule-creator-guide/concepts/c_rule-design-patterns.dita" xtrc="codeph:17;220:57">guide</codeph>, and
      rule 1 is a sentinel rule that always passes (for example, the
      "description-must-exist" check from Pattern 1). The inversion workflow
      is:</p>

      <codeblock xml:space="preserve" class="+ topic/pre pr-d/codeblock " xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/rule-creator-guide/concepts/c_rule-design-patterns.dita" xtrc="codeblock:9;225:39">{
  "name": "title-must-not-contain-guide",
  "steps": "S-5,5-D,F-1,T-5,5-M,M-E",
  "fix": "Remove the word 'guide' from the title."
}</codeblock>

      <p class="- topic/p " xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/rule-creator-guide/concepts/c_rule-design-patterns.dita" xtrc="p:13;231:10">Rule 5 passes when <codeph class="+ topic/ph pr-d/codeph " xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/rule-creator-guide/concepts/c_rule-design-patterns.dita" xtrc="codeph:18;231:37">guide</codeph> IS present (the bad state).
      The True branch (word found) loops back to rule 5, which fails the
      workflow. The False branch (word absent — the good state) routes to the
      sentinel rule 1, which passes. The workflow therefore passes when and
      only when the word is absent.</p>

      <p class="- topic/p " xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/rule-creator-guide/concepts/c_rule-design-patterns.dita" xtrc="p:14;237:10"><b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b " xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/rule-creator-guide/concepts/c_rule-design-patterns.dita" xtrc="b:3;237:13">Verify the inversion with both documents before committing the
      rule set.</b> Use the REPL to confirm each case explicitly:</p>

      <ol class="- topic/ol " xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/rule-creator-guide/concepts/c_rule-design-patterns.dita" xtrc="ol:1;240:11">
        <li class="- topic/li " xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/rule-creator-guide/concepts/c_rule-design-patterns.dita" xtrc="li:1;241:13">
          <p class="- topic/p " xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/rule-creator-guide/concepts/c_rule-design-patterns.dita" xtrc="p:15;242:14"><b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b " xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/rule-creator-guide/concepts/c_rule-design-patterns.dita" xtrc="b:4;242:17">Failing case</b> — a document whose H1 contains "guide":</p>
          <codeblock xml:space="preserve" class="+ topic/pre pr-d/codeblock " xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/rule-creator-guide/concepts/c_rule-design-patterns.dita" xtrc="codeblock:10;243:43">md-validate repl
&gt; load docs/bad-guide.md
&gt; eval title-must-not-contain-guide</codeblock>
          <p class="- topic/p " xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/rule-creator-guide/concepts/c_rule-design-patterns.dita" xtrc="p:16;246:14">Expected result: <codeph class="+ topic/ph pr-d/codeph " xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/rule-creator-guide/concepts/c_rule-design-patterns.dita" xtrc="codeph:19;246:39">FAIL</codeph>. If the result is PASS, the
          True/False branches are swapped — invert the routing.</p>
        </li>
        <li class="- topic/li " xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/rule-creator-guide/concepts/c_rule-design-patterns.dita" xtrc="li:2;249:13">
          <p class="- topic/p " xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/rule-creator-guide/concepts/c_rule-design-patterns.dita" xtrc="p:17;250:14"><b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b " xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/rule-creator-guide/concepts/c_rule-design-patterns.dita" xtrc="b:5;250:17">Passing case</b> — a document whose H1 does not contain "guide":</p>
          <codeblock xml:space="preserve" class="+ topic/pre pr-d/codeblock " xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/rule-creator-guide/concepts/c_rule-design-patterns.dita" xtrc="codeblock:11;251:43">&gt; load docs/clean-title.md
&gt; eval title-must-not-contain-guide</codeblock>
          <p class="- topic/p " xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/rule-creator-guide/concepts/c_rule-design-patterns.dita" xtrc="p:18;253:14">Expected result: <codeph class="+ topic/ph pr-d/codeph " xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/rule-creator-guide/concepts/c_rule-design-patterns.dita" xtrc="codeph:20;253:39">PASS</codeph>. If the result is FAIL,
          the sentinel rule (rule 1) is not passing on its own — verify it
          in isolation with <codeph class="+ topic/ph pr-d/codeph " xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/rule-creator-guide/concepts/c_rule-design-patterns.dita" xtrc="codeph:21;255:37">eval description-must-exist</codeph>.</p>
        </li>
      </ol>

      <p class="- topic/p " xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/rule-creator-guide/concepts/c_rule-design-patterns.dita" xtrc="p:19;259:10">Add a comment in the rule set JSON above the workflow to explain the
      inversion and include a migration note for the v0.3 upgrade. See
      <xref href="c_workflow-language-overview.dita#c_workflow-language-overview/inversion-antipattern" class="- topic/xref " xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/rule-creator-guide/concepts/c_rule-design-patterns.dita" xtrc="xref:11;261:105" type="section"><?ditaot usertext?>Workflow inversion anti-pattern</xref>
      for the full failure-mode analysis.</p>
    </section>

  </conbody>
